The defendant Kimberly B Warp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Conceal (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kimberly B Warp in court with attorney William J. Reddin.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to count #1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. Case #15CM1143 is dismissed and read-in to this case. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Reddin makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT#1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

120 DAYS JAIL (STRAIGHT TIME)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

____No contact with store listed in the Criminal Complaint
____No violent contact with the Victim listed in 15CM1143
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Continue current treatment
____Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

FINE:  $515.00 + $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME: 35 days-Non-working hours with standard release conditions, STAYED, for use of agent with court permission.
advising the Court that the defendant will resolve this matter on October 12, 2015, with attached correspondence on defendant's behalf filed by Attorney Reddin.
